04:08.879 --> 04:11.227
Beautiful lawns...

04:11.251 --> 04:12.829
Spacious homes...

04:12.853 --> 04:16.303
Happy families...

04:16.327 --> 04:18.365
These are the hallmarks
of suburbia,

04:18.389 --> 04:22.238
but if you look beneath
the veneer of gracious living,

04:22.262 --> 04:25.312
you will see a battle raging...

04:25.336 --> 04:27.474
A battle for control.

04:27.498 --> 04:29.946
You see the combatants
everywhere...

04:29.970 --> 04:32.949
Engaged in their routine
skirmishes... Get outta here!

04:32.973 --> 04:35.722
Fighting fiercely
to have dominion

04:35.746 --> 04:37.724
over the world around them,

04:37.748 --> 04:40.727
all the while knowing...

04:40.751 --> 04:43.560
It's a battle they will lose.

04:43.584 --> 04:45.371
Oh, hey, honey, um,
just stick that anywhere.

04:45.395 --> 04:47.364
I'll take care of it.

04:47.388 --> 04:50.297
Wow. It's really pilin' up.

04:50.321 --> 04:53.269
Oh, uh, don't worry.
I have a system.

04:53.293 --> 04:55.402
Really?

04:55.426 --> 04:57.704
Yeah, every two days, I clean.

04:57.728 --> 04:59.376
Two days.

04:59.400 --> 05:02.549
Yeah, I let the mess accumulate
for two days,

05:02.573 --> 05:05.317
and then I clean until
it's sparkling, and then, uh,

05:05.341 --> 05:07.314
the cycle starts all over again.

05:07.338 --> 05:08.885
And why...

05:08.909 --> 05:11.057
Have I never seen
the sparkling part?

05:11.081 --> 05:13.620
Well, because by the time
you get home from work,

05:13.644 --> 05:15.571
the boys have
messed everything up again.

05:15.595 --> 05:19.326
See? That's what I would call
a flaw in the system.

05:19.350 --> 05:20.667
What are you doin'?

05:20.691 --> 05:22.829
I think I'm asking you
to clean the house.

05:22.853 --> 05:25.340
Really? 'Cause it sounds to me
like you're criticizing me.

05:25.364 --> 05:27.974
No.

05:27.998 --> 05:30.628
No, no, no, no. No.

05:33.404 --> 05:36.413
I'm not saying
it has to be sparkling.

05:36.437 --> 05:38.485
How many times did I come home
to a mess

05:38.509 --> 05:40.487
and I never said a word?

05:40.511 --> 05:42.519
Please, don't take this
the wrong way.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.500
I think you are doing a terrific
job, but let's be clear.

05:44.524 --> 05:47.754
When you came home,
it was to clutter.

05:47.778 --> 05:50.597
I mean, come on, this is...

05:50.621 --> 05:52.621
More than that.

06:01.031 --> 06:03.670
Look at him, just chatting away.

06:03.694 --> 06:06.413
So inconsiderate.

06:06.437 --> 06:09.115
Phyllis, we've only been
waiting here for two minutes.

06:09.139 --> 06:11.778
I told you when we left
the house that I needed to eat.

06:11.802 --> 06:13.580
I have low blood sugar.

06:13.604 --> 06:15.491
Do you wanna see me keel over?

06:15.515 --> 06:18.124
No... in theory.

06:18.148 --> 06:20.927
Here you are.

06:20.951 --> 06:23.460
Thank you.

06:23.484 --> 06:26.032
By the way, Mrs. Van De Kamp,

06:26.056 --> 06:27.834
I heard about
your husband's passing.

06:27.858 --> 06:29.736
I'm so sorry. Dr. Van De Kamp

06:29.760 --> 06:31.768
was one of my favorite
customers, truly.

06:31.792 --> 06:34.040
That's very sweet of you.
Thank you.

06:34.064 --> 06:36.448
I'm not just being polite,
Mrs. Van De Kamp.

06:36.472 --> 06:37.744
How are you feeling?

06:37.768 --> 06:39.746
Well, Mr. Pashmutti...

06:39.770 --> 06:43.770
We're holding up as best
we can under the circumstances.

06:45.636 --> 06:48.785
I'm sorry. This is,
uh, Rex's mother, Phyllis.

06:48.809 --> 06:51.458
I'm so sorry about your son.

06:51.482 --> 06:55.492
Thank you. You know, the hardest
thing is to lose a child.

06:55.516 --> 06:57.494
I can't even imagine.

06:57.518 --> 07:00.026
Come on, Phyllis. Let's get you
something to eat.

07:00.050 --> 07:04.471
We had no warning. I was doing
dishes when I got the call.

07:04.495 --> 07:05.972
Really?

07:05.996 --> 07:10.577
Phyllis, there are
people waiting, so come on.

07:10.601 --> 07:13.580
Excuse me. I... I'm so sorry,

07:13.604 --> 07:15.582
but my son just passed away.

07:15.606 --> 07:17.584
Oh, I'm so sorry.

07:17.608 --> 07:18.745
Thank you. I mean,

07:18.769 --> 07:21.087
I was telling
Mr. Pashmutti here,

07:21.111 --> 07:24.591
my life is... is over.

07:25.576 --> 07:29.546
My life is over.

07:31.622 --> 07:34.601
This is ridiculous,
you know that? Pen.

07:34.625 --> 07:36.863
Don't you think I have
better things to do

07:36.887 --> 07:39.105
than to bring you checks
every day,

07:39.129 --> 07:41.107
checks that I could be
signing at home?

07:41.131 --> 07:43.439
This one's dry.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.580
You know, taking away
my access to our account,

07:44.604 --> 07:46.573
that's just vindictive.

07:46.597 --> 07:49.546
Thank you. Do you
know how long it takes me

07:49.570 --> 07:50.947
to schlep out here
to this hellhole?

07:50.971 --> 07:52.679
Exactly. It's the only way
I can guarantee

07:52.703 --> 07:54.681
you'll come and visit me.

07:54.705 --> 07:56.683
That's ridiculous.
You're my husband. I love you.

07:56.707 --> 07:58.755
Obviously, I would come visit.

07:58.779 --> 08:00.757
I thought it was obvious
that when you love someone,

08:00.781 --> 08:03.490
you wouldn't have an affair.
I was wrong, wasn't I?

08:03.514 --> 08:06.633
I'm getting really tired
of this song, Carlos.

08:06.657 --> 08:08.635
Isn't it about time
you forgave me?

08:08.659 --> 08:12.198
You want my forgiveness,
you got it. My trust...

08:12.222 --> 08:14.200
That you're gonna have to earn.

08:14.224 --> 08:16.207
Be careful, Carlos.
Up until now,

08:16.231 --> 08:18.204
I've been really lonely
in that big bed of ours,

08:18.228 --> 08:21.648
but when you're rude to me, it
makes me wanna be not so lonely.

08:21.672 --> 08:23.650
Comments like that
are exactly why

08:23.674 --> 08:25.221
you'll never again
have access to my money.

08:25.245 --> 08:27.053
Why are all rich men jerks?

08:27.077 --> 08:29.177
The same reason
all beautiful women are bitches.

08:32.913 --> 08:34.861
So same time tomorrow?

08:34.885 --> 08:36.684
Sure, baby.

08:42.222 --> 08:43.799
What do you mean, you know?

08:43.823 --> 08:46.533
I mean, I know.

08:46.557 --> 08:48.535
What are you saying, that
your father actually told you

08:48.559 --> 08:51.838
he was gonna be having a one
night stand with Edie britt?

08:51.862 --> 08:53.680
Uh, mom, this wasn't
a one night stand.

08:53.704 --> 08:56.688
He's been going out with Mrs.
Britt for a few months now. What?

08:56.712 --> 08:59.846
How could you not tell me that?
We share everything.

08:59.870 --> 09:02.549
That's what we're known for.
That's our thing.

09:02.573 --> 09:04.691
Because I knew you'd wig out.

09:04.715 --> 09:07.594
Besides, haven't you always told
me to respect people's privacy?

09:07.618 --> 09:09.596
Oh, I've never
applied that concept

09:09.620 --> 09:12.158
to your father's sex life,
and you know it. Are you done?

09:12.182 --> 09:16.703
No! I have not even begun
ripping into Edie britt yet.

09:16.727 --> 09:19.566
Oh, that peroxide vulture.

09:19.590 --> 09:21.838
I just know as sure
as I am standing here

09:21.862 --> 09:25.772
that she went after your father
just to tick me off.

09:25.796 --> 09:26.973
Wrong again. What?

09:26.997 --> 09:28.675
He asked her out.

09:28.699 --> 09:30.647
You lie. It's true.

09:30.671 --> 09:32.318
He called her for a date
six months ago...

09:32.342 --> 09:35.582
The day after my birthday party.

09:35.606 --> 09:37.584
The one at the piano bar?

09:37.608 --> 09:39.726
Yeah.

09:39.750 --> 09:43.189
What is it? Oh, um...

09:43.213 --> 09:45.200
Your father
just came over that day

09:45.224 --> 09:47.193
and told me some stuff.

09:47.217 --> 09:50.566
You know, some stuff
that I haven't...

09:50.590 --> 09:52.038
And can't tell you.

09:52.062 --> 09:55.602
Wait. Whatever happened to
"we share everything"?

09:55.626 --> 09:57.674
Isn't that our thing,
what we're known for?

09:57.698 --> 10:02.348
Um, actually, I think what we're
known for is sharing clothes.

10:02.372 --> 10:05.682
Yeah. I think that's our thing.

10:22.392 --> 10:26.202
Why does he keep doin' that?

10:26.226 --> 10:29.906
He knows it's annoying.

10:29.930 --> 10:31.708
He's just trying to get to us.

10:31.732 --> 10:33.802
Yeah, well, it's working.

10:41.211 --> 10:44.250
Knock it off, down there,
do you hear what I'm saying?!

10:44.274 --> 10:47.684
Matthew. Matthew!

10:49.379 --> 10:50.719
Sit down.

10:57.828 --> 11:00.837
You know we don't talk to him.

11:00.861 --> 11:03.940
That's part of his punishment.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.651
How can you just sit here
hour after hour

11:06.675 --> 11:08.174
and listen to that?

11:08.198 --> 11:13.119
Well, that's part of mine.

11:30.390 --> 11:32.368
Carlos, what is this
big emergency?

11:32.392 --> 11:35.432
I had to cancel my hair
appointment with Eduardo today.

11:38.028 --> 11:40.106
Baby, what is it?

11:40.130 --> 11:43.179
I'm completely freaked out.

11:43.203 --> 11:45.211
Why?

11:45.235 --> 11:49.215
There's this guy,
his name's Richie,

11:49.239 --> 11:51.718
and he's been
saying some stuff to me,

11:51.742 --> 11:54.020
and I'm gettin' worried.

11:54.044 --> 11:56.823
Honey, you and your macho pride.

11:56.847 --> 11:58.995
Just tell him you're flattered,
but you don't swing that way.

11:59.019 --> 12:02.929
He's not hitting on me,
you idiot, he's threatening me.

12:02.953 --> 12:05.271
Really? How?

12:05.295 --> 12:07.403
He said he's gonna beat me up

12:07.427 --> 12:09.075
unless I come up
with some money.

12:09.099 --> 12:11.077
Well, how much money?

12:11.101 --> 12:12.238
$7,000.

12:12.262 --> 12:14.841
$7,000?! Keep your voice down.

12:14.865 --> 12:17.243
Why would he think
you have that kind of money?

12:17.267 --> 12:20.747
Because yesterday, in a visiting
room filled with criminals,

12:20.771 --> 12:23.119
my wife referred to me
as a rich man.

12:23.143 --> 12:26.052
Oh, right. Sorry.

12:26.076 --> 12:28.054
That's why I needed you
to bring the checkbook.

12:28.078 --> 12:30.326
He's actually willing
to take a check?

12:30.350 --> 12:31.858
No.

12:31.882 --> 12:34.906
You're gonna take the money
to his girlfriend,

12:34.930 --> 12:37.433
and if she doesn't get it
by tomorrow, I'm screwed.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.465
Honey, I think
this is a mistake.

12:39.489 --> 12:41.467
If we give in to extortion,

12:41.491 --> 12:43.739
the guy's just gonna keep
coming back for more money.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.972
What choice do I have?

12:45.996 --> 12:48.744
You're a strong guy.
You went to college

12:48.768 --> 12:50.847
on an athletic scholarship,
for god sakes.

12:50.871 --> 12:53.371
Yeah, it was for golf.

12:55.175 --> 12:56.875
Oh.

13:01.511 --> 13:04.060
You have all my pants.

13:04.084 --> 13:07.934
Yeah, I know. Come on in.

13:07.958 --> 13:12.768
I, uh, thought when I took
my stuff back to my house

13:12.792 --> 13:14.270
I got everything.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.834
Oh, it's fine.
They're in the garage.

13:19.830 --> 13:22.879
So how have you been doing?

13:22.903 --> 13:25.083
Good. Um... I'm, uh, good.

13:28.408 --> 13:31.117
I got a question for ya.
Sure, what is it?

13:31.141 --> 13:34.060
Where are we now? Where are we?

13:34.084 --> 13:36.071
Yeah. We're not
moving in together

13:36.095 --> 13:40.086
and we're not broken up,
so where are we?

13:43.593 --> 13:46.372
I don't know.

13:46.396 --> 13:49.906
Since the guy
who held me hostage

13:49.930 --> 13:51.908
turned out to be your son,

13:51.932 --> 13:54.210
I think logic dictates
that I should move on.

13:54.234 --> 13:56.482
The problem is...

13:56.506 --> 13:59.145
I'm crazy about you.

13:59.169 --> 14:02.118
So...

14:02.142 --> 14:05.852
So I'm thinking we should
keep it casual.

14:05.876 --> 14:06.993
Casual.

14:07.017 --> 14:11.357
What the hell does that mean,
exactly, um, casual?

14:11.381 --> 14:13.359
Uh...

14:13.383 --> 14:16.062
Well, I-I don't...

14:16.086 --> 14:18.064
I don't think there's
anything wrong with us

14:18.088 --> 14:20.066
seeing a movie once in awhile.

14:20.090 --> 14:25.471
A movie. Okay. Is that it?

14:25.495 --> 14:28.474
Jogging?

14:28.498 --> 14:31.517
There's no law against jogging.

14:31.541 --> 14:35.021
Anything else?

14:35.045 --> 14:38.885
Shopping. That's casual.
That's fun.

14:38.909 --> 14:40.887
Anything else we can do?

14:40.911 --> 14:43.551
Anything at all?

14:46.056 --> 14:48.434
Mmm, brunch.

14:48.458 --> 14:49.958
Brunch would be nice.

14:56.066 --> 14:59.296
Sounds good to me.

15:07.207 --> 15:09.916
All I can do is take it
one day at a time.

15:09.940 --> 15:13.419
Yes.

15:13.443 --> 15:17.063
Oh, okay. Well...

15:17.087 --> 15:19.525
Thanks so much for calling.

15:19.549 --> 15:22.528
Who was that?

15:22.552 --> 15:26.432
Oh, someone named Alan hanley.

15:26.456 --> 15:29.505
My electrician?

15:29.529 --> 15:31.507
Why were you on the phone

15:31.531 --> 15:33.209
sobbing to my electrician?

15:33.233 --> 15:35.220
Oh, he called to offer you
his condolences.

15:35.244 --> 15:38.044
Then why didn't you put me on?

15:38.068 --> 15:42.048
Oh, well, we got to talking,
and then he had to go.

15:42.072 --> 15:47.053
He... he had some very beautiful
things to say about Rex.

15:48.378 --> 15:50.056
For god sakes, Phyllis,

15:50.080 --> 15:52.058
don't you ever worry
about dehydration?

15:52.082 --> 15:55.031
Are you saying
that I am too emotional?

15:55.055 --> 15:58.134
I'm saying that even Italians
take a break now and again.

15:58.158 --> 16:03.069
My son is dead. I'm grieving.

16:03.093 --> 16:05.216
So am I, but no one
would ever know it

16:05.240 --> 16:07.213
with your incessant
caterwauling.

16:07.237 --> 16:08.944
Bree!

16:08.968 --> 16:10.946
People want to know
how I'm doing,

16:10.970 --> 16:12.448
but the minute they ask,

16:12.472 --> 16:14.450
you... you jump
into the spotlight,

16:14.474 --> 16:16.622
and they forget all about me.

16:16.646 --> 16:19.485
I need consoling, too, Phyllis.
Have you ever thought of that?

16:19.509 --> 16:24.090
I'm sorry.

16:24.114 --> 16:26.292
It won't happen again.

16:26.316 --> 16:27.633
Thank you.

16:27.657 --> 16:28.964
Of course,

16:28.988 --> 16:30.997
if you didn't constantly
suppress your emotions,

16:31.021 --> 16:33.399
people wouldn't forget
to console you.

16:33.423 --> 16:35.501
Excuse me?

16:35.525 --> 16:38.674
Well, it's true. You're stoic
to the point of being cold.

16:38.698 --> 16:40.676
I am not cold. I just...

16:40.700 --> 16:43.509
Well, I don't like
public displays of emotion.

16:43.533 --> 16:45.011
Well, that's fine,

16:45.035 --> 16:47.413
but people wonder

16:47.437 --> 16:49.585
why they haven't seen you cry.

16:49.609 --> 16:53.059
I mean, some people
actually wonder

16:53.083 --> 16:55.661
if you truly mourn Rex.

16:55.685 --> 16:58.424
People have said that?

16:58.448 --> 17:01.448
A few, yes.

