35:46.315 --> 35:48.215
I don't know.

35:50.319 --> 35:52.126
But I can promise you
this much...

35:52.150 --> 35:55.400
I have never loved another woman
the way I loved you.

35:55.424 --> 35:58.803
You walked out on me.

35:58.827 --> 36:01.436
Yeah, but look how far I got.

36:01.460 --> 36:03.608
I'm just up the street.

36:21.310 --> 36:23.628
Mommy, mommy,
thank god, you're home.

36:23.652 --> 36:27.592
Hey, sweet pea.
Why? What's wrong?

36:27.616 --> 36:29.594
Daddy found a rat.

36:29.618 --> 36:33.798
Oh, did he now?

36:33.822 --> 36:37.302
Honey?

36:42.200 --> 36:43.378
I'm home.

36:43.402 --> 36:46.281
Hey, babe. Hey.

36:46.305 --> 36:47.882
Hi, how was your day?

36:47.906 --> 36:51.236
It was good, but,
more importantly, how was yours?

36:52.881 --> 36:55.220
Parker told you
about the rat, huh?

36:55.244 --> 36:57.292
Yep.

36:57.316 --> 36:58.623
Oh, my god,
it was so disgusting.

36:58.647 --> 37:00.625
I came down the steps,

37:00.649 --> 37:03.328
and there it was,
sitting on the counter

37:03.352 --> 37:05.970
eating a leftover
grilled cheese sandwich.

37:05.994 --> 37:08.403
The sandwiches from yesterday?

37:08.427 --> 37:10.405
Okay, yes, the house
has been too messy.

37:10.429 --> 37:13.338
Obviously, my system
has some kinks in it.

37:13.362 --> 37:15.440
But check it out.
I got my act together.

37:15.464 --> 37:16.611
Wow.

37:16.635 --> 37:17.812
So, um,

37:17.836 --> 37:20.315
I take it you took
the rat outside?

37:20.339 --> 37:22.587
Oh, no,
I smashed it with a shovel.

37:22.611 --> 37:24.489
You killed it?

37:24.513 --> 37:27.522
Not with the first blow.

37:27.546 --> 37:31.016
Whew. Disgusting.

37:50.769 --> 37:53.278
Hey...

37:53.302 --> 37:54.819
Little guy.

37:54.843 --> 37:56.821
I just wanted to say

37:56.845 --> 38:00.685
I'm really sorry
about what happened...

38:00.709 --> 38:02.757
With the shovel.

38:02.781 --> 38:05.530
Neither one of us
saw that coming.

38:05.554 --> 38:07.541
I know
it's not much consolation,

38:07.565 --> 38:10.635
but you really helped
my marriage.

38:10.659 --> 38:15.640
That's a lot for a little rat
to accomplish in one lifetime.

38:15.664 --> 38:20.645
Well, it's getting late, so...

38:20.669 --> 38:22.499
Hat's off to ya.

38:34.613 --> 38:37.600
So you'd say the abuse started
a few years into your marriage?

38:37.624 --> 38:40.595
It started so slowly,

38:40.619 --> 38:43.619
I didn't realize
what was happening.

38:45.354 --> 38:48.441
I mean, he'd slap me
over some little problem.

38:48.465 --> 38:50.335
But he'd always apologize.

38:50.359 --> 38:51.676
Then it got worse.

38:51.700 --> 38:53.778
And one day,

38:53.802 --> 38:59.444
eight years ago, my son
spilled soda on our new carpet.

38:59.468 --> 39:01.446
Before I could move
to protect him,

39:01.470 --> 39:03.718
Virgil had knocked him
on the ground

39:03.742 --> 39:05.820
and began kicking him.

39:05.844 --> 39:11.426
I wanted to protect my baby,
but I didn't get there in time.

39:11.450 --> 39:13.358
What happened to your son?

39:13.382 --> 39:17.001
Well, he died.

39:17.025 --> 39:19.404
I came across one of
his baby pictures last weekend.

39:19.428 --> 39:23.738
That's when the nightmares
started again.

39:23.762 --> 39:28.342
The last doctor I saw said that
I needed to let go of my guilt,

39:28.366 --> 39:31.376
and then I would
start sleeping again.

39:31.400 --> 39:34.118
Of course, that's easier said
than done.

39:34.142 --> 39:37.552
And I am getting so tired.

39:39.408 --> 39:44.789
I'm gonna start you
on nitrazepam.

39:44.813 --> 39:46.861
That should do the trick.

39:46.885 --> 39:48.693
Thank you.

39:48.717 --> 39:51.566
I certainly hope your husband
was punished for what he did.

39:51.590 --> 39:56.140
Oh, there was retribution.

39:56.164 --> 40:00.004
I made sure of that.

40:12.941 --> 40:14.919
Where are you off to?

40:14.943 --> 40:16.970
I'm, uh, I'm going to see
Rex's lawyer.

40:16.994 --> 40:21.766
We're going to go over some
details involving Rex's will.

40:21.790 --> 40:24.529
Phyllis...

40:24.553 --> 40:28.032
Obviously, I'm just mortified
over slapping you.

40:28.056 --> 40:32.507
I've... I've just been in
a weird place

40:32.531 --> 40:35.440
since Rex's death, but...

40:35.464 --> 40:38.443
That's no excuse.

40:38.467 --> 40:41.185
I'm very, very sorry.

40:41.209 --> 40:43.417
No need to apologize.

40:43.441 --> 40:47.421
You're family. All's forgiven.

40:47.445 --> 40:50.525
Really?

40:50.549 --> 40:52.527
It's been a difficult time
for all of us.

40:52.551 --> 40:55.429
I totally understand.

40:55.453 --> 40:56.931
Now, go.

40:56.955 --> 41:01.485
You don't want to be late for
your meeting about Rex's will.

41:24.913 --> 41:28.493
Claims. This is Joe flannery.

41:28.517 --> 41:30.535
Hello, um,
could I speak to someone

41:30.559 --> 41:31.596
about the death benefits

41:31.620 --> 41:33.598
for Rex Van De Kamp, please?

41:33.622 --> 41:36.200
This is his mother.

41:36.224 --> 41:39.911
Yes, uh, we've already spoken
to his wife several times.

41:39.935 --> 41:42.476
We are moving as quickly
as we can.

41:42.500 --> 41:46.840
Are you aware that my
daughter-in-law has a boyfriend?

41:49.678 --> 41:52.016
I'm listening.

41:52.040 --> 41:54.719
Control...

41:54.743 --> 41:59.923
It's extraordinary the tactics
people employ to obtain it.

42:02.290 --> 42:06.871
Some rely on deception.

42:06.895 --> 42:12.506
While others engage
in outright trickery.

42:12.530 --> 42:17.511
Then there are those
who resort to extortion.

42:17.535 --> 42:21.085
Why do we fight so hard
for control?

42:22.240 --> 42:24.919
Because we know to lose it

42:24.943 --> 42:28.953
is to put our fate
in the hands of others.

42:30.579 --> 42:33.579
And what could be
more dangerous?
